Topic Fundamental Rights

QUESTIONS



Enumerate the distinguishing features of three fundamental rights and three principles of policy each. 

Article 8 of the constitution says that the senate shall not make any laws with or in derogation of fundamental rights, whereas, Art. 233 gave the state power to suspend fundamental rights. Do you think that both the provisions are inconsistent with each other? Give your arguments.

To be treated in accordance with law is the inalienable rights of the citizen. What particular rights are safeguarded and under what Article of Constitution of Pakistan?

Explain the following fundamental rights (enshrined under): 

Art. 17, 19, 10, 25, 19-A, 10-A, 25-A, 1, 8, 4.

What is the wisdom and importance (significance) of having Fundamental Rights under the constitution? Discuss in detail with reference to important law on the subject. 

What do you understand by fundamental rights? Elaborate Art. 19.

Draw a distinction between concept of right and fundamental rights. Discuss Art. 25 of the Constitution.















FUNDAMENTAL RIGHTS WITH THEIR DISTINGUISHING FEATURES

FUNDAMENTAL RIGHTS

Meaning of Right  

Right means legally guaranteed powers available to a legal entity in realization or defense of its just and lawful claims & interests (such as individual freedom) against the whole world. 

Meaning of Fundamental Rights

Fundamental rights are a group of rights that have been recognized by the Supreme Court as requiring a high degree of protection from government encroachment. These rights are specifically identified in the Constitution.

Points of Demarcation

Fundamental Rights are guaranteed by the Constitution, whereas, Ordinary Rights are guaranteed by Ordinary Law. 

Fundamental Rights are enforceable even against the government, whereas, Ordinary Rights are not enforceable against the government. 

Fundamental Rights are of wider scope, whereas, Ordinary Rights are of narrow scope as compare to the former.

WISDOM, IMPORTANCE, OR SIGNIFICANCE OF FUNDAMENTAL RIGHTS

Is that they are most essential for the attainment by the individual of his full intellectual, moral, and spiritual status. The object of conclusion of them in the constitution is to establish a government of law and not of man









FUNDAMENTAL RIGHTS WITH THEIR DISTINGUISHING FEATURE

U/A 8(1): LAWS INCONSISTENT WITH FUNDAMENTAL RIGHTS ARE VOID-

Law, custom, or usage have the force of law.

  

U/A 8(2): LAW WHICH ABRIDGE THE RIGHTS-

Shall not be made by the state. 

U/A 8(3): EXCEPTIONAL CASES WHERE ART.8 SHALL NOT APPLY-

Any law relating to members of armed forces or of police charged with maintenance of public order;

Other laws specified in part 1 of the Fundamental Schedule.   

U/A 8(4): LEGISLATURE SHALL BRING THE LAWS IN TO CONFORMITY- 

With the rights conferred under this chapter; 

Within a period of 2 years from the commencing day. 

U/A 8(5): EXTENSION IN THE SAID PERIOD OF 2-YEARS-

Of maximum 6-months through resolution of the legislature.  

U/A 9: SECURITY OF PERSONS-

No person shall be deprived of life and liberty;

Save in accordance with law. 

U/A 10(1): SAFEGUARD AS TO ARREST AND DETENTION-

No detention without mentioning grounds of arrest;

Opportunity of defense by a legal practitioner.

U/A 10(2): PRODUCTION BEFORE MAGISTRATE WITHIN A PERIOD OF 24-HOURS-

Excluding the time necessary for journey. 

U/A 10(3): PERSON DETAINED UNDER THE LAW OF PREVENTIVE DETENTION- 

Clause 1 & 2 shall not apply to such person.

U/A 10(4): THE LAW OF PREVENTIVE DETENTION SHALL APPLY ONLY TO THE PERSON- 

who acts in a manner prejudicial to the integrity and defense of Pakistan, external affairs of Pakistan;

No detention for a period exceeding 3-months unless reviewed and extended by the Revenue Board. 

U/A 10(5): COMMUNICATION OF THE GROUNDS OF DETENTION-

to the detenue within a period of 15-days; 

and affording him an opportunity of making representation; 

Authority may refuse to disclose grounds if it is against the public interest.  

U/A 10(6): FURNISHING OF COPY OF ORDER TO THE REVIEW BOARD- 

by the authority passing such order;

Unless secretary to the Government issue a certificate to the contrary. 

U/A 10(7): NO PREVENTIVE DETENTION FOR A TOTAL PERIOD OF MORE THAN 8-MONTHS AND 12-MONTHS- 

If a person is detained for an act prejudicial to public order and any other case respectively. 

U/A 10(8): DETERMINATION OF PLACE OF DETENTION AND SUBSISTENCE ALLOWANCE- 

For the family of the detenue by the Review Board.

U/A 10(9): NON-APPLICATION OF THIS ARTICLE TO ALIEN ENEMY. 

U/A 10-A: RIGHT TO FAIR TRIAL- 

And due process in Civil as well as Criminal proceedings.

U/A 11(1): SLAVERY & FORCED LABOR PROHIBITED- 

and no law shall permit or facilitate it in Pakistan;

all forms of forced labor and human trafficking is prohibited;

no children below the age of 14 shall be employed;

No application of this law to person undergoing punishment.  

U/A 12: PROTECTION AGAINST RETROSPECTIVE PUNISHMENT- 

no punishment for an act or omission that was not punishable by law at time of act or omission;

No penalty greater than the penalty prescribed by law for that offence at the time the offence was committed. 

U/A 13: PROTECTION AGAINST DOUBLE PUNISHMENT-  

no person shall be prosecuted or punished for the same offence more than once;

No person accused of an offence shall be compelled to be a witness against himself.  

U/A 14: DIGNITY OF MEN- 

and privacy of home shall be inviolable;

No torture for the purpose of extracting evidence.  

U/A 15: FREEDOM OF MOVEMENT, ETC.-

any citizen may move freely throughout Pakistan; and

May reside or settle. 

U/A 16: FREEDOM OF ASSEMBLY- 

peaceful and without arms assembly;

Subject to some restrictions of public order. 

U/A 17: FREEDOM OF ASSOCIATIONS, UNIONS ETC.- 

subject to some restrictions imposed by law;

every person except in service of Pakistan has the right to become a member of a political party;

but if prejudicial to the interest of Pakistan, the Federal government shall refer the matter to the Supreme Court;

Every political party shall be accountable for the source of its funds in accordance with law.  

U/A 18: FREEDOM OF TRADE, BUSINESS, OR PROFESSION-  

Every citizen has the right if it is lawful and requirements have been fulfilled, (if any). 

U/A 19: FREEDOM OF SPEECH, ETC.- 

freedom of speech, expression, press, etc.;

Subject to some restrictions e.g., contempt of court, glory of Islam, defense, security, and integrity of Pakistan. 

U/A 19-A: RIGHT TO INFORMATION-   

in all matters of public importance;

Subject to regulation and restrictions. 

U/A 20: FREEDOM TO PROFESS RELIGION-

and to manage religious institutions;

