In respect of religious institutions other than one’s own religion.

U/A 23: PROVISION AS TO PROPERTY- 

right to acquire, hold, and dispose of property in any part of Pakistan;

Subject to constitution and other restrictions.

U/A 24: PROTECTION OF PROPERTY RIGHTS. 

no person shall be deprived of his property save in accordance of law;

Except acquired by the government after making payment for public purposes. 

U/A 25: EQUALITY OF CITIZENS- 

and are entitled to equal protection of law;

no discrimination on the basis of sex;

Government passes right to make special provisions for the protection of women and children.

U/A 25-A: RIGHT TO EDUCATION- 

free and compulsory education;

To all children ranging from 5 to 18 years.

U/A 26: ACCESS TO PUBLIC PLACES-

non-discrimination in respect of access to public places;

On ground of age, religion, caste, and sex etc. 

U/A 27: DISCRIMINATION IN SERVICES- 

there is safeguard against it;

person otherwise qualified shall not be discriminated on the ground of age, religion, caste, and sex etc.;

Specific posts shall be reserved for that specific class or sex without which it cannot be performed.  

U/A 28: Preservation Of Language, Script, Or Culture-

Subject to Art. 251, any section of citizens shall have the right to preserve.

