Difference Between RIOTING AND AFFRAY

Rioting

Affray

AS TO NUMBER OF PERSONS AND OBJECT.

In rioting five or more persons do unlawful act in prosecution of common object by force or violence.

In affray two or more persons fight with each other without common objective.

AS TO PLACE.

Rioting may be committed in a private place.

Affray is always committed at public place. 

AS TO PUNISHMENT.

Whoever commits rioting shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two (2) years or fine or both.

Whoever commits affray shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one month or three thousand rupees fine or both.

