--- START OF FILE: Difference between robbery & dacoity.docx ---

DIFFERENCE BETWEEN

ROBBERY & DACOITY

DIFFERENCE

ROBBERY

DACOITY

NUMBER OF PERSONS.

In Robbery-the number of persons are less than FIVE (5). It may be committed by a single person. 

Whereas, in Dacoity-the number of persons are Five (5) or more.  

SERIOUSNESS.

Robbery is less serious in nature in compare to Dacoity.

Whereas, the Dacoity is more serious offence than robbery because of the terror caused by the presence of number of offenders.

POSITION OF ABETTORS.

In Robbery-the abettors are liable independently. 

Whereas, in Dacoity-abettors who are present and aiding, when the crime is committed, are counted in the number.

JURISDICTION OF COURTS.

Robbery may be tried by the area (Ilaqa) Magistrate. 

Whereas, Dacoity shall be tried by the court of Sessions. 

PUNISHMENT. 

Whoever, commits robbery shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than THREE (3) years nor more than TEN (10) years and shall also be liable to fine. 

Whereas, the court while convicting a person u/s 395 can either sentenced him to imprisonment for life, or to rigorous imprisonment which cannot be less than FOUR (4) years or more than TEN (10) years in addition to fine. 

POSITION ON THE HIGH WAY.

If the Robbery is committed on the Highway-the imprisonment may be extended to 14 years. 

Whereas, the fact that Dacoity is committed on the Highway-does not change the nature or term of the punishment.

--- END OF FILE: Difference between robbery & dacoity.docx ---


--- START OF FILE: Difference between theft & extortion.docx ---

DIFFERENCE BETWEEN 

THEFT AND EXTORTION

DIFFERENCE

THEFT

EXTORTION

AS TO CONTRACT.



In the Theft-the offender’s intention is to take the movable property in a person’s possession dishonestly without his consent. 



Whereas, In the Extortion- the offender intentionally puts a person in fear of any injury to him or to any other person and thereby, dishonestly induces the person put under fear to deliver to any person any property or valuable security. 

AS TO PROPERTY.



In the Theft- only movable property is the subject of the theft. 



Whereas, In the Extortion-both movable and immovable properties maybe the subject of the extortion.  



AS TO ELEMENT OF FORCE.



There is no element of force in the Theft.



Whereas, there is an element of force in the offence of Extortion as the property is obtained by putting a person in fear of any injury to that person or any other person.

AS TO SCOPE.



The Theft covers only the cases of movable property.



Whereas, the Scope of Extortion is wider than the Theft, as it covers: any kind of property, valuable security, or anything that may be converted into valuable security.

AS TO TAKING OF PROPERTY.



In Theft- property must be moved by a person in order to commit such taking.  



Whereas, In Extortion-threat may be made by one person and property maybe received by another person.

AS TO EFFECT.



In the Theft-there is dishonest removal of property.



Whereas, In the extortion-the property is delivered under influence of fear.  



AS TO PUNISHMENT.

(SAME)

Whoever commits Theft shall be punished with imprisonment which may extend to Three (3) years or with fine or with both.



Whoever commits extortion shall be punished with the imprisonment which may extend to THREE (3) years or with fine or with both.

