THE USE OF:

IS TO, AM TO, ARE TO, WAS TO, WERE TO.

Zamana Haal keliye.

Is to/am to/are are used in sentences in which any work is considered necessary to be performed. 

Nashani: Urdu sentences ke end par ‘na hai’ jaise alfaz atai hain. Like-

Examples: 

ENGLISH TRANSLATED SENTENCE

URDU PHRASE

I am to/was to complete my syllabus timely. 

Mujhe apna nasab waqt-e-muqarra par muqamel karna hai/karna tha.



Pakistan is to/was to fight against atomic powers. 

Pakistan ko atomi kowato se muqabala karna hai/karna tha.



NOTE 1:

Above mentioned if made in past then Nashani is ‘na tha’ and was to/were to as helping verb will be used.    





















THE USE OF:

HAS TO, HAVE TO, HAD TO.

NOTE 1:

 In present tense has to/have to are used in those sentences in which any work needs to be done out of necessity. 

Nashani: Urdu sentences ke akhar par ‘parta hai’ jaise alfaz atain hain. Like-

Examples: 

ENGLISH TRANSLATED SENTENCE

URDU PHRASE

We have to/had to cover a lot of syllabus to pass the examination. 

Humain Imtian pass karne keliye buhat sara nasab cover karna parta hai/parta tha.

