269: NEGLIGENT ACT LIKELY TO SPREAD INFECTION OF DISEASE DANGEROUS TO LIFE

Whoever unlawfully or negligently does any act which is, and which he knows or has reason to believe to be, likely to spread the infection of any disease-dangerous to life, shall, be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to 6 months, or with fine, or both.   

Negligently doing any act known to be likely to spread infection of any disease dangerous to life

May arrest without warrant 

